<subSubSection id="DBBC5D437D764E28074739BDC4F540F8" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6CEC09AC286304606ACAC992F8476E25" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03A5971F68809A16BDC092E78A25D5F9" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
This is new record to Zhejiang. The species is one of the most widely distributed species in China while its relatives are restricted to rather smaller areas. The main differences between these species affect the male characters (see 
<bibRefCitation id="F77BE98D5CDF6D72341158D114BE55EF" author="Tang, L" journalOrPublisher="Zookeys" pageId="39" pageNumber="86" pagination="65 - 78" title="On Scaphidium grande-complex (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Scaphidiinae)." url="10.3897/zookeys.43.447" volume="43" year="2010 a">Tang and Li 2010a</bibRefCitation>
). The Taiwanese records of the species are based on 
<taxonomicName id="21E6F601A49DFFC5034354C1B8933F00" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium grande" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="grande">Scaphidium grande</taxonomicName>
var. inimpressum Pic which was synonymized by 
<normalizedToken id="4A1E5E67FEE44E2E6B213C9900D1CEEE" originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
in 1992. Several specimens in our collection from Taiwan are considered to be a closely related species of 
<taxonomicName id="B17E6E338F0B539BA9E3D1E08A789620" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium grande" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="grande">Scaphidium grande</taxonomicName>
, and this might imply that 
<taxonomicName id="72DCBAF6E8CA32E12F2C9DC3C90CAB4F" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium grande subsp. inimpressum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="grande" subSpecies="inimpressum">Scaphidium grande inimpressum</taxonomicName>
Pic is a good species. To clarify the doubt, a study on the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="643EA26F8ADE8A1FCFDB4B709EA5D43D" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium grande subsp. inimpressum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="grande" subSpecies="inimpressum">Scaphidium grande inimpressum</taxonomicName>
Pic and more related material from Taiwan will be necessary; the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="A8CF372910B145C5CD3B85BB74AD577F" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Scaphidium grande" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="grande">Scaphidium grande</taxonomicName>
in Taiwan is now doubtful.
</paragraph>
